  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Medical students' abilities to diagnose skin lesions after dermatology electives often remain
      unsatisfactory despite a dermatology elective being one of the most effective ways to improve
      their clinical reasoning. Feedback and reflection are two basic teaching methods used in
      clinical settings. This study aimed to investigate the effectiveness of structured reflection
      and immediate feedback in improving of medical students' evaluation of skin lesions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
